t; therefore is ext2fs suddenely trying to write from non existant pages and<br />&gt; "Oops..."  messages galore as well as a mess that e2fsck moans about a fair<br />&gt; bit but seems to fix.<br /><br />This should be fixed in 1.3.77: the bug was trivial. I just hadn't even _heard_<br />of the problem before, so there is some lack of communication from somebody.<br /><br />(I'm not on all the mailing lists, and I don't have time to read all the<br />newsgroups, so if there are problems like this people should cc them to me)<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
